    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Omnicom Venture To Get New Chief</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Patricia Winters Lauro</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Lauro, Patricia Winters</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tom Cotton is leaving as J Walter Thompson executive vice president and president for global business to join DDB Worldwide in new post of president of DDB Ventures (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Tom Cotton, a top executive at J. Walter Thompson in New York, part of the WPP Group, is leaving to join DDB Worldwide in New York, part of the Omnicom Group, in the new post of president at DDB Ventures.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Tom Cotton, a top executive at J. Walter Thompson in New York, part of the WPP Group, is leaving to join DDB Worldwide in New York, part of the Omnicom Group, in the new post of president at DDB Ventures.</p>
        <p>At DDB Ventures, Mr. Cotton, 47, will oversee the development of ideas for businesses and services that the agency can develop, acquire or jointly own with other companies. Mr. Cotton had been an executive vice president at Thompson and president for global business; he was also director in charge of big accounts like Qwest Communications International and Merrill Lynch. He had also worked at agencies like Geer, DuBois; Backer &amp; Spielvogel; and Foote, Cone &amp; Belding.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
